Collection of Personal Data
This Personal Data Protection Notice (“Notice”) is issued to all our valued customers/prospective customers, pursuant to the requirements of the Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (“PDPA”).
We treat and view your personal data seriously.
In the course of your dealings with us, TGV Cinemas Sdn Bhd and its related corporations (as defined under the Companies Act 2016) (“TGV Group”, we”, “us”, “our”), we will request that you provide data and information about yourself (“Personal Data”) to enable us to enter into a transaction with you or to deliver the necessary notices, services and/or products.
This Notice serves to inform you that your Personal Data is being processed by us or on our behalf and you hereby give your consent to the processing of your Personal Data.
Nature of Personal Data
The Personal Data that we collect from you may include information concerning your name, age, identity card number, passport number, address, gender, date of birth, marital status, occupation, income range, contact information, email address, race, ethnic origin, nationality, credit card details, next of kin, employer, bankers and other personal data we collect from you on any subsequent occasion.
Impact from failure to supply Personal Data
It is obligatory that you supply us the details marked with asterisk (*) in our registration form (collectively, “compulsory Personal Data”).  The failure to supply such compulsory Personal Data will:-
result in us being unable to provide you with the notices, services and/or products requested;
result in us being unable to accept and process your entry to any contest;
result in us being unable to update you on our latest products, services and promotions.
Purpose of Collecting Personal Data
The Personal Data is collected, used and otherwise processed by us for, amongst others, the following purposes:
processing your request(s), order(s), purchase(s) and/or contest entry;
delivering notices, services, products, updates, prizes and/or promotional materials to you;
maintaining and improving customer relationship;
conducting marketing survey and client profiling activities;
maintaining and updating internal record keeping;
detecting and preventing crime (including and not limited to fraud, money-laundering, bribery);
meeting any legal or regulatory requirements and making disclosure under the requirements of any applicable law, regulation, direction, court order, by-law, guideline, circular, code applicable to us or any entity within TGV Group;
enabling us to send you information by email, telecommunication means (telephone calls, text messages, in-app notifications or app pushes) or social media (organic posting or paid advertisements) about products, services and/or promotions offered by TGV Group and selected third parties that we think may interest you; and
such other purposes directly related to the foregoing,
collectively the “Purposes”.
Source of Personal Data
Your Personal Data is being or is to be collected:
from the cookies embedded on our website, application or any other related tracking mechanism that may be deployed by us from time to time;
when you register as a member of our loyalty programme;
when you log in to your account;
when you contact our customer service centre;
when you submit your Personal Data to us for any of the Purposes stated above;
from all other Personal Data we collect from you on any subsequent occasion; and
from all other information that you may provide us from time to time.
Disclosure
The Personal Data provided to us will be kept confidential and you hereby consent and authorise us to provide or disclose your Personal Data to the following categories:-
any person to whom we are compelled or required to do so under law;
any entity within TGV group;
payment channels including and without limitation, financial institutions for purpose of assessing, verifying, effectuating and facilitating payment of any amount due to TGV Group in connection with your acquisition of our services and/or products;
our business partners and affiliates that provide related services or products in connection with our business, for joint promotions and/or contest;
statutory authorities, government agencies and industry regulators;
our consultants, accountants, auditors, lawyers or other financial or professional advisers;
our sub-contractors or third party service or product providers;
our service providers for purposes of establishing and maintaining a common database where we have a legitimate common interest;
the general public when you become a winner in a contest by publishing your name, photographs and other Personal Data, without compensation for advertising and publicity purposes.
Safeguards
We shall keep and process your data in a secure manner. We endeavour, where practicable, to implement the appropriate administrative and security safeguards and procedures in accordance with the applicable laws and regulations to prevent the unauthorised or unlawful processing of the Personal Data and the accidental loss or destruction of, or damage to, the Personal Data.
Rights of Access and Correction
Subject to the provisions of the PDPA, you may, upon payment of a prescribed fee, have the right to request access to and correction of your information held by us and in this respect, you may:
Check whether we hold or use your Personal Data and request access to such data;
Request that we correct any of your Personal Data that is inaccurate, incomplete or out-of-date;
Request that your Personal Data is retained by us only as long as necessary for the fulfilment of the purposes for which it was collected;
Request that we specify or explain our policies and procedures in relation to data and types of Personal Data handled by us;
Communicate to us your objection to the use of your Personal Data for marketing purposes whereupon we will not use your Personal Data for these purposes; and
Withdraw, in full or in part, your consent given previously, in each case subject to any applicable legal restrictions, contractual conditions and a reasonable time period.
We may refuse to comply with a data access request or a data correction request and shall, by notice in writing, inform you of our refusal and the reasons of our refusal.
The department to whom written requests for access to the Personal Data or correction and/or deletion of the Personal Data or for information regarding policies and procedures and types of Personal Data handled by us is:
Attention to: Customer Service
Email:
feedback@tgv.com.my
Address: Level 28, Menara Maxis, Kuala Lumpur City Centre, 50088 Kuala Lumpur.
You may also unsubscribe to our marketing materials by clicking the unsubscribe link contained in the email we send to you and following the instructions therein.
Third Party Personal Data
We may require your assistance if the Personal Data relating to other persons is required to process your Personal Data for the Purposes, and you hereby agree to use your best endeavour to assist us when required. In the event that Personal Data of any third party is supplied by you to us, you shall ensure that such third party has read this Notice and consented to us collecting his/her Personal Data for any of the Purposes prior to the supply of his/her Personal Data to us.
Transfer of Personal Data to Places outside Malaysia
We may transfer your Personal Data to a place outside Malaysia and you hereby give your consent to the transfer.
Accuracy of Personal Data
You are responsible for ensuring that the information you provide us is accurate, complete, not misleading and kept up to date.
Conflict
In the event of any inconsistency between the English version and the Bahasa Malaysia version of this Notice, the English version shall prevail over the Bahasa Malaysia version.
